reviews.text: Very good Cheung Fan!  Usually sold out before noon.
Love the wonton noodles n beef brisket curry rice, with almond milk soup. So yummy

This was the first stop in Hong Kong for breakfast. We came here because it was really close to the hotel. It wasn't too busy so we were able to get a seat straight away.
We ordered in English and there wasn't a problem. Food was interesting. The cheong fun was nice but a bit too soft for my liking. The macaroni soup with cha shiu was tasty. They also had congee and other delicacies. Seemed like a place where locals would normally eat.
可以坐半個鐘，都冇人走來問你食啲乜，我坐係度又如一件物件!
該店提供很多的粉麵飯食品，煲仔菜亦有多欵，他們的例湯也不錯，員工的服務態度也很好
